    # "He had been a brickmaker before the fall of Rosanna and claimed to have once worked on Castle Reinmeer. He says he remembers her, the princess."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_cc291ed5:
    # "Sarah does not speak."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_cc090c0e:
    # "Looking across the tent, she finds hateful eyes gazing at her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_1db3ce58:
    # "Perhaps the others believe him. Perhaps they simply go along with him. The result is the same."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_660c1ccb:
    # "They seize her and pull her towards the center of the tent."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_fb6577e0:
    # "Looking out across the sea of faces, Sarah can see in their hollow eyes that none will raise a finger to save her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_8418ef3f:
    # "They hold a trial, so much a mockery that it cannot even be called that in jest."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_72eb16d3:
    # "Her punishment, to be a slave to the slaves."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ba720115:
    # "They hate her. In her they see the cause of their circumstance. They see in her the reason for why they and their families have been made so low."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_8c4c35d7:
    # "And they carry out their hatreds on her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_05e29e01:
    # "In the midsts of the crowd, the gang of men seize on her body."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ce9d40c4:
    # "She does not fight them, for it is pointless."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_fb27372c:
    # "For as many others as there are, there are only witnesses, no saviors."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_53e0f384:
    # "The man who first accused her, takes her first, but the others swiftly follow."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_6e996cff:
    # "By the end of the night, Sarah has long lost count."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_e108914f:
    # "For three nights, the men delight in their new found status."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_be4307c9:
    # "Then, reality asserts itself."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ac4b9a5f:
    # "The fourth day begins with the shouting of guards."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_831be465:
    # "All the slaves, Sarah among them, are startled by their violent screams."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_d4e3529e:
    # "They wade through the tent and one by one, they pull up the men of the gang."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_6e80161b:
    # "It's odd, Sarah thought as she looks at them. How timid they now look."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_540cdd81:
    # "The men of the gang are pulled out towards the center of the tent and bound by the tribesmen."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_3e8c80d7:
    # "They gesture and yell, towards her, towards them. Nobody speaks the language, but everyone understands."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_41f6d52a:
    # "The men expect the whip."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_3a4b5e39:
    # "They expect it because they were fools and did not know the law of their new land."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_002e5e5d:
    # "Now, they would be the instruments of teaching that new law to all who witnessed."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_9627857d:
    # "Bound and held in place, the men are unable to run or even struggle much at all."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_8d0788f8:
    # "They grab the leader first."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0e4e8c54:
    # "The blade is pulled up and glimmers for a moment in the light of the embers of the campfire."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_4cc90ca3:
    # "The tribesman reaches between the leaders legs and swipes the blade."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_18026f37:
    # "A blood-curdling scream rings out across the silenced mass of slaves."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_1fd9edb4:
    # "Blood runs down his legs as he writhes in their grasp."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_57dcd6ba:
    # "He could not have known the punishment of the tribes for his actions, but he had to suffer it all the same."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_8c5b479a:
    # "As he screams, the tribesman holds up his severed member for all to see."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_46318e82:
    # "Having made his point, he casually tosses the former leader's manhood into the campfire."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c0e928d4:
    # "It crackles like pork to the grill."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0f14ac75:
    # "The other members of the gang now understanding their fate, struggle, scream and beg."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_6b86df4e:
    # "The blade comes for them all the same."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_3cebae3f:
    # "In less than a few minutes, all the men of the gang have been unmade."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_e9f49de1:
    # "And Sarah sees the delight in the eyes of the other slaves."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_fff94ee9:
    # "To see these wicked men punished in turn, even though none of them had raised a finger to stop them."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_d4f11c88:
    # "Sarah realized that as the fortunes turned, so did the estimations of the other slaves."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_cf44259c:
    # "A justice of some kind, the others would whisper among themselves."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_08e9964b:
    # "But in truth, the tribesmen wanted to guard their wealth."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_40aa6e8e:
    # "Sarah was a slave, one among many, but she held value. As a beautiful woman, she held more than most."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_db2ac3b0:
    # "The men and their actions had threatend that value, for a pregnant slave was worth only a quarter of one that could still work."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_5b1c6db4:
    # "And what did the tribesmen care for the desires of slaves?"
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_4c782a51:
    # "Had it not been too much effort, they would have undid all the men of Rosanna."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0d366e7f:
    # "But they understood that this was not needed. The message had been send, and all understood."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c1e8b9bb:
    # "The men of Rosanna lowered their heads and muted all notions of rebellion, so deep struck the fear of the punishment."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_bf6e3685:
    # "The slaves became slaves in their hearts as well."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_4daf9d47:
    # "The members of the gang whithered and faded into themselves. Only keeping their heads low. Everywhere they went, the people whispered."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ed0c29f0:
    # "Sarah had no more trouble from them."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c9a7719e:
    # "Those Rosannan men who had previously dared the occasional encounter, voluntary or otherwise, had now grown fearful."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_eaa1f3ad:
    # "Instead, they internalized their new roles."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_da85bc6d:
    # "At night, near the edges of the tent, gone were the sounds of moaning pleasure."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_2e559d6e:
    # "Instead, Sarah now would see the men, hunched over, working themselves."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_5d8788fc:
    # "Their seed spilled impotently on the earth, where it would never take root."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_d89dbe8b:
    # "But over time, this came to be understood by them as natural."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_e1f1a8c3:
    # "The women belonged to the tribesmen. And the men had neither the ability nor the will to risk fighting for them."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f063f909:
    # "And as the tribesmen visited and took the women of their choosing, they were often defiant."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_d26a4046:
    # "Taking the women in the midsts of the crowd, they displayed with arrogance the difference in power."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_8c060c12:
    # "Still, the men only lowered their gaze, and spend their nights by themselves."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_02ab2401:
    # "To her own surprise, Sarah saw the momentum change in the tent in ways that she had not expected."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_a1f9453a:
    # "The women had hated the tribesmen at first, but now they seemed to hate their own husbands, fathers and brothers more."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_506dd8b3:
    # "They hated them for how they allowed all of this to happen."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_409227dc:
    # "The tribesmen took them, for this was their nature. But were the men of Rosanna not made of honour and chivalry?"
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c7c5bba4:
    # "All their lives, the women remembered being told as much."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_95867ab0:
    # "That men were of such nature, and women of another nature, and this justified all the ways in which they were treated differently."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_23d0c9d8:
    # "Well, what of it now then, the women wondered in unison?"
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_809081e0:
    # "Had they not been loyal to their natural fate? So why then did now the men abandon their supposed role?"
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_779030a6:
    # "Instead, all they saw in the faces of their own men, was weakness."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_8bac98e3:
    # "Weakness as they watched their wives, sisters and daughters be taken by the conquerors."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c8b8bb2a:
    # "And they did not blame them for failing to free them, for how could any one man resist all the horde."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_b470b9be:
    # "But they blamed them for how meekly they allowed it all to happen."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_5d37634f:
    # "How quickly they became the slaves they had been forced to become."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_7f3262fa:
    # "Their hatreds for their men began to fester and emerge in many ways."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_04e1e6f5:
    # "They gossiped about them. Insulted them. Laughed at them."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_8f5b5c75:
    # "If resistance had ever been an option, the men did not seize on it now any more than for any of the countless proceeding insults."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ca0d031d:
    # "The women laughed and pointed at the men who gathered at night near the edge of the tent to pleasure themselves."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_9d1110d2:
    # "They hurled insults at them, taunted them with stories of how much greater the tribesmen were than them."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_49df4804:
    # "And each night, the men spilled their seed into the earth, lowered their heads, and said nothing."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_94ef7183:
    # "So, the women of Rosanna became lost to the men of Rosanna."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_8c1324f3:
    # "They hated their new masters still, but they hated their own men more."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_308fe180:
    # "They delighted in knowing the pain they inflicted on them, each time another girl was married off to a tribesmen."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f2e6cfe9:
    # "And they whispered among one another, that whatever else, at least a tribesmen would fight for you."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_1607cc27:
    # "As the last tether broke between them, the women began to more openly seek the favors of the tribesmen."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_4af2147b:
    # "There was nothing that remained, they realized. No future that one could hope for with a Rosannan man."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_4cc5486e:
    # "But with a tribesmen, despite everything, one could have a life."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_4aa4a439:
    # "Away from the slave tent, in his house. Bear him a child and you would almost be of equal standing to any other woman of their tribe."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_a7c6a9b1:
    # "Sarah watched as the girls began to become ever more open in their ambitions."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0b794210:
    # "What the tribesmen once took by force, they now received freely."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_a4e285fa:
    # "Among the tribes, a man could take many wives, and for those soldiers who had fought in the war, it was expected."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f0814923:
    # "The women of Rosanna did not object even to something that appeared so barbaric."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_58ac323e:
    # "They joked among themselves, rather to share one tribesmen than be left with a Rosannan man all to yourself."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c09bd6e1:
    # "As the weeks passed, the numbers of women slowly dwindled."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_d1caa34e:
    # "The prettiest were the first."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_16ba27f8:
    # "Those who had the hints of fertility were soon to follow."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_aec8aa65:
    # "In the end, only the men and the older women remained. Fit only for service."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_86bd8aef:
    # "And the older women hated the men the most, for they had wasted all their lives on these men who now proved so lacking."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_55275203:
    # "The men, for their part, still gathered near the edge of the tent at night."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_dba4b6d2:
    # "Huddled in silence, they worked themselves to fantasies of what the tribesmen had in reality."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c9f0b371:
    # "They spilled their seeds to the infertile earth."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_bfead360:
    # "Sarah, beautiful and young, had captured the interest of a tribesmen soldier some time in the third week."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_b0762037:
    # "He had first caught her eye, for his body was still in the prime of youth."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_01d8d836:
    # "Not all women were so lucky as to find a man their own age."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_e961fe5f:
    # "While his body had first caught her eye, it was his nature that caused her to sway."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c2044638:
    # "In a harsh place like this, his was oddly gentle."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ce42ff4d:
    # "He brought her flowers from the desert, and she eagerly put them in her hair."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_e47a23c8:
    # "In this empty place, they had felt to her as jewelry."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_cbe0ae2d:
    # "As day after day, she was collected and made to work until nightfall, Sarah had found herself surprised."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_22456923:
    # "Before, her days had been a blur, passing her by in such a way that she could hardly recall what had happened."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_3e9588de:
    # "Now, her mind had become present again, and she found it often wandering towards the tribesman soldier."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_e625c0c0:
    # "When he would come to her, her heart ran fast in her chests. When he failed to show, she felt herself nearing to tears."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f5d940e0:
    # "Her love for him had come to her in subtle ways, and she was surprised even when she finally dared to admit it to herself."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ca4a1148:
    # "She had feared that he might learn or know of what had transpired before. That this might ruin her in his eyes."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_9d949e66:
    # "But if he knew, he gave no hint of it. And his estimation of her never wavered."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_5c04b013:
    # "Their courtship had ran little more than two weeks."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_04f9810a:
    # "In Rosanna, such a speed would have been considered improper, but here it revealed a surprising restraint on his part."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_a569a606:
    # "She knew he could force her, but in his eyes she saw how he regared her with wonder, and knew he never would."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_9d3b163a:
    # "Neither spoke the other's language, and so their courtship passed with only smiles and gestures."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ee0f8a2e:
    # "When her suitor finally purchased her, the passing of coins happened out of her sight."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_b4856ebd:
    # "Sarah was no fool to the nature of their relationship, but she was thankful that she did not need to witness her own sale."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_fd8da7b3:
    # "Though she was his by right, property in their society, she could feel in his every touch that he loved her as well."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_16ff5b1d:
    # "He collected her from the slave tent."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_da83710c:
    # "As he walked her out of the tent and into the warm desert air of a setting sun, he turned to her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0e484d82:
    # "His powerful hands, already calloused from war, gently wrapped around her neck, as if he feared even the slightest touch might injure her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_57d942cf:
    # "Then, with a loud clicking noise, he unbound the chains that had kept her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_1e934e13:
    # "She was still a slave to him, but he gave her this first kindness."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_64c02e33:
    # "She turned and gave one last glance towards the slave tent that she had spend all these weeks in."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_4911dfd8:
    # "Sarah left it all behind her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_2f6862cf:
    # "She would never return to this place, for the rest of her life."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_243d9f47:
    # "And with it, she would leave all the horrid memories of that place and its people."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_3b634362:
    # "She ceased to be Rosannan."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_cb7463eb:
    # "His home was humble, but compared to where she had been before, it was like a palace."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_e80cea5e:
    # "Sarah properly washed and bathed herself for the first time in a long time, without the peering eyes of other slaves."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_4ab614d0:
    # "The return of privacy was instant and unmistakable. Something that had felt so normal, now appeared to be so valuable."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_8b4be00e:
    # "When she exited the bath, she found to her own surprise a set of clothes in the other room."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f4767456:
    # "For so long she had wandered around naked, that she had almost forgotten that it was unnatural to her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_188e01f4:
    # "As her fingers ran gently across the soft white fabric of the dress, she marveled at its beauty."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_3261961c:
    # "Interwoven and standing out against the white design of the dress, were the multitude of bright desert flowers that were unfamiliar to Sarah."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_a35f6ea7:
    # "A bride in Rosanna was clad in white only, like a ghost, but here they crowned their brides in bright floral, for all the world to see."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_93627812:
    # "She smiled as she allowed her eyes to run across it again and again."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_478db66e:
    # "She held back even her fingers, fearing that to touch it any further might undo even a single perfect strand."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_9984931e:
    # "He had no need of such ritual. She was already his by right, and she would have given herself willingly to him."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_dd0aa5b4:
    # "Instead, she understood that this was a promise of him to her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_7e1e405b:
    # "That there would be more here than mere lust."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0ed3f9e7:
    # "When Sarah put on the dress, crowned in flowers, she went out and met her husband."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_515b9ee9:
    # "Smiles and gestures were their only weak to communicate, for neither could speak the other's language, but it proved enough."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_7ea43ad3:
    # "The words were spoken, the rituals carried out, and by end of day she was his wife and he her husband."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_b7eeb91f:
    # "Later that evening, they retired to his bed."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ce1d3962:
    # "At first, they fumbled and stumbled in the ways of newlyweds. But with perseverance, each began to understand the other."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c1858c42:
    # "Some acts required no language."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_a9542f73:
    # "Deep into the night, Sarah allowed herself to explore what all her life had been forbidden from her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_2132986a:
    # "She had feared this had been ruined to her by the violence of her own people, but she found in him all things inversed."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_24cb2506:
    # "Despite his strength, his touches were soft. Despite his rough hands, they felt gentle to her skin. Despite his fierceness, soft eyes."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_4bf02e4f:
    # "All things in him were measured and balanced, and she felt above all, safe."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0809b22a:
    # "Entwined in the arms of her new husband, she collapsed on top of him."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f054a396:
    # "Sweat ran down her back, cooled by the cold night air of the desert."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_20643617:
    # "Beneath her, she felt the iron chest of her husband, rising and falling, seemingly equally content."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0743ba2e:
    # "His powerful arms, wrapped around her, she felt as though nothing would ever hurt her again."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_56d56ac1:
    # "In the years that followed, Sarah taught him a few words of her own language, which he spoke softly to her in secret."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c30e4abd:
    # "He taught her the language of his people."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0a3f6537:
    # "As she learned the language, the world opened up to Sarah."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ed6a4b9c:
    # "The markets, no longer strange places to her, now appeared exciting and alive. She haggled with the shopkeepers, enjoying the game of it."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_9c511582:
    # "With the privacy of her own home, the dignity of clothes and the connection of language, Sarah slowly began to feel at home in this new place."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_67188f84:
    # "They had practiced a degree of restraint, her husband choosing to finish outside of her most evenings."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_37d8a3db:
    # "But such measures were imperfect, and two years past their marriage, Sarah recognized the many changes of her body."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0ad782d8:
    # "She knew the signs in the way all women know."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_a8123daa:
    # "Her life had become impossibly filled with a happiness she had long thought lost to her. Now she feared what a child might do to upset this delicate balance."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_2d5ba960:
    # "When the swelling of her belly had become so obvious even men could understand, she sat down with her husband."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_9c838cd0:
    # "Fear ran deep in her chest and throat as she told him."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_84c5c52d:
    # "But in his eyes, only wonder."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f85a61c3:
    # "If she had ever imagined she knew love, she would forever remember it was a faint imitation compared to what she now saw in his eyes."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_2db9370d:
    # "He seized her within his broad and strong arms, spinning her around."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c62b4344:
    # "He only put her down when she warned him that he ought to be careful with her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_7aa1a7aa:
    # "As the months moved on and Sarah felt her body swell further, the many inconveniences of pregnancy besetting her, she found her husband ever waiting for her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_ae355334:
    # "He lingered near her, constantly dotting on her, hoping only that by being near he could be of service to his wife for only a brief moment."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_5d53f974:
    # "Forever in awe at the miracle of her body."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_6b7172ee:
    # "And Sarah, fearing that her growing body would cause her husband to wander, found him only ever more faithful to her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_a3a59328:
    # "When she looked at herself in the mirror, she was sad at what had become of her firm body."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_e6cc9dc8:
    # "And yet, when she looked at herself through the eyes of her husband, she swore that she could nearly see a halo about herself."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_2bcd9cdc:
    # "Over time, she began to see herself as her husband did, and allowed herself to feel that same happiness."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f42c5d58:
    # "When the moment of the birth came upon them, the many elderly women from the tribe came from all over to guide a new mother on her first steps."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_6069e07e:
    # "The men, useless in moments like these, were ushered out and seemed almost grateful to be told to leave."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f5d2958d:
    # "For several hours, she laboured, but in the end she managed."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_7e4e8078:
    # "A son."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_02ea0328:
    # "Nearing exhaustion, Sarah thought she had desired only sleep, until she beheld the miracle that she and her husband had brought forth, and longed only to hold him."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_cb19a466:
    # "She managed for a brief moment, before exhaustion carried her to sleep."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_a94b39b0:
    # "It was only early the next day when she awoke again, her child neatly bathed and swaddled."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_70cee334:
    # "Sarah, speaking no words, reached out with her hands and one of the elder women delivered her child to her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c3ebe8cd:
    # "Holding him in her arms, Sarah looked down at this new life which moved her heart deeper than she had ever imagined possible."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_5b61c776:
    # "How she had ever managed to find joy in a place like this, she could not recall, only that she had."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_7333381f:
    # "When a few moments later, her husband joined her on the bed, Sarah could feel her heart close to bursting."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c5690e83:
    # "This was a joy so abundant, it felt wrong not to share."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_c79aa512:
    # "Together, they must have sat there for close to the entire day, staring only in pure worship at this small new creature that now ruled their hearts."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f510ed1f:
    # "It would prove the first of their children, and many followed."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_eb0ac9ee:
    # "Though Sarah tried to teach them the small ways of her own people, she could not deny that as they grew, they were children of the tribes."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_74e3ac91:
    # "And with each passing year, she regarded herself in the mirror, and saw less of her own people reflected in herself."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_7ce865b2:
    # "With the passing of the years, eventually, she had spend more time living among the tribes than she ever had in Rosanna."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_0438de2a:
    # "If it gave her cause to concern, it never lasted long."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_5428b5ac:
    # "Her growing family was forever a distraction in which she eagerly endulged."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_79037843:
    # "So the years passed and her family grew. The many children she bore her husband, made her only grow in his estimation."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_01f8d734:
    # "In his face she saw the passing of the years, and she learned to love the many marks that ran deeper with every cycle."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_f6bef85d:
    # "Forever reflected back at her in his eyes, she saw the deepening of his love towards her."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_60290271:
    # "So ends the story of Sarah Rose."
    ""

translate ru SingOrNot_6e51cdff:
    # "A princess turned slave. A slave turned wife. A wife turned mother."
    ""

